rComments: I hope to grow into a professor just like Prof. Wang in the future.
organized, smart, and full of spirit. an absolute inspiration.

His understandin of the field is superb. His willingness to aid in the understanding the subject and correcting misconceptions is outstanding. He is always willing to schedule time to consult personal problems with course and grades.
A pleasure to have him as a professor! He has what it takes to be a good/considerate educator, very helpful and never give it up until you understands.
I swear, this man has the memory of an elephant.  He'll remember your name, your face, and possibly your grades from last year/term.  That, and he used to have a saggy car. :)
HE KILLS CHALK! :O... Otherwise totally awesome.

this guy is amazing. great prof, really smart. very respectful of everyone. great guy. study, the guy recycles questions like mad. plus his T/F contain double negatives and stuff. you don't even understand the question. in multiple choice just choose the longest answer. in T/F choose false.
Prof. Wang is one of the best profs in the department, if not the whole engineering school.
really great guy. has a bit of a language barrier but compensates for it with repetition and articulation. Also a very practical prof.

When a prof says "If you don't understand this material, it is not your fault, it is my fault", it tells you, he really cares about the students. One of the best prof I've had the pleasure of learning from.
